<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t18560514-560">
               <interp inst="t18560514-560" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/18560514"></interp>
               <interp inst="t18560514-560" type="date" value="18560514"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18560514-560-charge-1" targOrder="Y" targets="def1-560-18560514 t18560514-560-offence-1 t18560514-560-verdict-1"></join>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18560514-560-charge-2" targOrder="Y" targets="def2-560-18560514 t18560514-560-offence-2 t18560514-560-verdict-1"></join>
               <p>560. <persName id="def1-560-18560514" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-560-18560514" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-560-18560514" type="age" value="25"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-560-18560514" type="surname" value="SMART"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-560-18560514" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-560-18560514" type="occupation" value="carman"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">HENRY SMART</hi>
                  </persName>
                  <rs id="t18560514-560-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18560514-560-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18560514-560-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="stealingFromMaster"></interp>, stealing 28lbs. weight of rags, 30 plates, 7 dishes, and other articles, the goods of <persName id="t18560514-name-631" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-631" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-631" type="surname" value="ANDREWS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-631" type="given" value="THOMAS CHARLES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-631" type="occupation" value="keeps a China shop"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18560514-560-offence-1 t18560514-name-631"></join>Thomas Charles Andrews</persName>, his master; and </rs>
                  <persName id="def2-560-18560514" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def2-560-18560514" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-560-18560514" type="surname" value="PERRIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-560-18560514" type="given" value="CHARLOTTE"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">CHARLOTTE PERRIN</hi>
                  </persName>
                  <rs id="t18560514-560-offence-2" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18560514-560-offence-2" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18560514-560-offence-2" type="offenceSubcategory" value="receiving"></interp>, feloniously receiving the same, knowing them to have been stolen.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. RIBTON</hi>. <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18560514-name-633" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-633" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-633" type="surname" value="ANDREWS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-633" type="given" value="THOMAS CHARLES"></interp>THOMAS CHARLES ANDREWS</persName>
                  </hi>. I keep a china shop and deal in rags at No. 16, Richard-street, Woolwich—Smart was in my service as carman over twelve months—I have missed a great quantity of rags and other goods, and I have called his attention to it—on 10th April I was called in to my dinner—I was busy, and was not more than ten minutes—I went to the front door and saw Smart coming across the road—I had ordered him not to leave the back door, and that gave me suspicion—he had a bag and a screw wrench with him—I said to him, "Where have you been?"—he said, "Over the way to borrow this wrench"—I said, "Where have you been with the bag?"—he said, "Round the comer"—I said, "Where?"—he said, "Round the corner," and began to be very insolent—I said, "I insist on knowing"—I took it from him, and found that rags had been in it—I said, "Where did you get it?"—he said, "From Dr. Stewart's"—I took him round to Dr. Stewart's, and I said to Dr. Stewart, in Smart's presence, "Have you seen my carter come in here?"—he said, "I have not, I have been sitting at the desk this last half hour, and no one has come in at all"—Smart appeared confused, and I said to him, "This satis-faction is not sufficient,"I took him to the station, and he was detained, and the inspector sent a policeman to make inquiries—I examined the bag and found some pieces of white ragin it—I went to the house of Mr. Seymour,</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="185605140328"></xptr>
               <p>who is a dealer in rags—some rags were shown to me there—I was able to identify two pieces as my property—one was a piece of dimity curtain, and the other was half a corded petticoat—I can swear to these, I had seen them amongst my own rags at my own place that morning—after that I went to Smart's lodging, which is at Perrin's house—I think it is called Myrtle-place—we saw Perrin—the sergeant asked her if a man lived there who worked for me—she said, "Yes"—he asked her what his name was?—she said, "Smart"—he said, "Have you got anything here belonging to him?"—she said, "No"—he said, "Are you sure of that?"—she said, "No"—we searched, and found some pans, which I identify as my property, with my mark on the bottom of them—I asked her where she got them from—she said she bought them at different shops—I said, "What shops? they are marked with my mark"—she said she did not know—I said, "They came from my shop"—she then said, "I will tell you all about it: Smart brought them in place of money for his board and lodging"—she said since Dec. he had not paid her any money—she said, "I will tell you all about it: here is some more in this box"—the box was then opened; it was a long trunk or box, like a clothes box, and in it was found this gilt tea service—these are things that have been in my place—they might have been sold—here is a dinner set—these things have at one time formed part of my stock—I will not undertake to say they have not been sold—here are six plates and other things—I can say the same with regard to them—here is a toy cup and saucer, which I can swear was in my place, and had never been sold—I had seen it in my place within two or three months—I missed it and spoke about it to all my men, and to Smart amongst the rest—here is a tea spoon, which I can swear was never sold; here is my mark on it—here is a square glass inkstand I can swear to—we sell these to Government, and supply cadets with them, no one else—when they came up I put them in a particular place—there were twenty-four of them, and I missed one of them—there were but twenty-three left—I had missed the one about a month before 10th April—here is a glass salt cellar, which I can identify—I find there is one of mine gone—with regard to this China tea service, I had not missed the teacups, but teapots and sugar basins I had missed—these pans are mine; I do not know when I missed them, we have five or six hundred at a time—I could not say how many rags I missed.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. DENNEY</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did you have any reference with Smart? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No, I took him without reference, because I knew he had worked for the parish—I paid him 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. a week—I did not form any suspicion of him at first—I had some suspicion of him for about three months, when I found things done up in different places, ready to take away—I think it was between 12 and 1 o'clock when I saw him at the door with the bag under his arm—he has not been in the habit of carrying a bag—he went out with goods in the pony cart—if any person came and bought a few things, and I had not another man, I would send him—when I asked him to go to the police station, he was very insolent at first—I said, "You must go"—he said, "Very well"—I knew where he lodged, a few doors from my back premises—I did not ask him if he bad any objection to his lodging being searched—I was not in the habit of entrusting him with goods for sale on commission—the back of my warehouse goes back into Myrtle-place—we unload vessels and bring up all our goods from the back—there is access to the premises from the back as well as the front—I have a number of men coming backwards and forwards—these are such articles as are not sold in Woolwich—there are not such articles as these there—I purchase them from</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="185605140329"></xptr>
               <p>Staffordshire, Yorkshire, and other places—if I saw these articles in Staf-fordshire or Yorkshire I could not swear to them—there are not articles of this pattern sold in Powis-street—I know some of these have not been sold—I do not know that Smart's father is in a large way of business at Maid<lb></lb>stone—I heard his father say he was sorry he was his son, he had behaved very badly to him—I can tell you how I came by this dimity, when rags are bought they are put into a basket, and I opened the bundle of rags to see what was in it, and I looked particularly at this piece of dimity and this corded petticoat in it, and when we went to get the rags I said, "If they are mine you will find a piece of dimity and a corded petticoat in it"—this is the corded petticoat, and this is the dimity—I know these two pieces were in the bundle when I opened it that same morning—I cannot tell who I bought these rags of—I buy of anybody—we know the persons as our customers—we have bought of strangers—I do not keep any books of these things—we have removed goods for Mr. Serjeant—I should not think it likely that he would leave any rags behind—I have no mark on this inkstand, but they are ordered to this one pattern for the cadets—we supply them to one person only.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. ROBINSON</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Is there any mark on the pans? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—they have been in my shop—I cannot say they have not been sold—I have supplied tea sets to a bazaar—these are common patterns—all the crockery was taken at Perrin's house.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. RIBTON</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Had Smart any authority to sell any goods of yours? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Never—I strictly forbade him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> What is the value of the whole of the property? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I put them down at 3<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. or 4<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. altogether—I never sold any of these articles to Smart—my daughter and two men and a boy all serve in my shop.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18560514-name-634" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-634" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-634" type="surname" value="SEMON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-634" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>MARY SEMON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the daughter of George Semon, a rag merchant, in Powis-street, Woolwich—Smart came to me on 10th April about 1 o'clock, with a bag of white rags with him—I gave him 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 11<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. for 28lbs.—I laid them down by the side of the door of the shed by themselves—these are them—shortly afterwards the prosecutor and the policeman came, I showed them the rags and they were taken away.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. DENNEY</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> How do you recollect it was on the 10th of April? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I went to the Court the same day—I had no other rags in the same place where these were—this is the bag they were brought in.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18560514-name-635" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-635" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-635" type="surname" value="NEWELL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-635" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN NEWELL</persName>
                  </hi>. (<hi rend="italic">policemen, R</hi> 59.) I went to Perrin's house when Smart was in custody—I put some questions to Perrin—she at first denied all knowledge of these articles, and then she said she would tell all, and she said Smart brought them there—I searched Smart at the station and found on him 8<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 10<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. and a key of Mr. Andrews' street door, which I gave to Mr. Andrews.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18560514-name-636" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-636" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-636" type="surname" value="ANDREWS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18560514-name-636" type="given" value="THOMAS CHARLES"></interp>THOMAS CHARLES ANDREWS</persName>
                  </hi>. I received this key and tried it to my street door—it was the key of that door—we had missed it for six weeks.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. DENNEY</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did you give Smart the key to get in and out? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No; I never did—I missed this key—it was a patent lock on the door—I spoke to the prisoner and the other men, they all said they knew nothing about it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">SMART</hi>—<hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <rs id="t18560514-560-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
